<h3><%= link_to "Smooth Data", smooth_tools_path  %></h3><hr><br/>
<p>
  The smoothing tool uses the 'rolling average' or 'windowed cutoff' algorithm to create a new sample. The rolling average uses a configurable window size. The windowed cutoff uses a supplied cutoff value and returns the number of inflection points that cross the cutoff within each window.
</p>
<h3><%= link_to "Create Ratio", new_synthetic_path %></h3><hr><br/>
<p>
  Build a Ratio sample from a combination of multiple sample sources.
</p>
<h3><%= link_to "Expression Viewer", expression_viewer_path %></h3><hr><br/>
<p>
  Select interesting samples to view a profile of the expression for each feature. Search on annotations and sort by counts. 
</p>
<h3><%= link_to "Blast", new_blast_path %></h3><hr><br/>
<p>
  Use the blast suite to compare your sequence against the database.
</p>